20/05/2003
BRUSSELS, Belgium -- Macedonian Defence Minister Vlado Buckovski and Foreign Minister Ilinka Mitreva went before the 19 NATO ambassadors to the North-Atlantic Council on Monday (19 May). They briefed them on implementation of the country's national action plan for NATO membership and presented the recently adopted strategy for national security and defence. In turn, the ambassadors urged full implementation of the Ohrid peace accord, emphasising that much more must be achieved in terms of economic growth, the fight against corruption and nepotism and especially the building of a multiethnic state.
In other news, the daily <I>Dnevnik</I> reported Tuesday that Nikola Gruevski, deputy chairman of Macedonia's main opposition party VMRO-DPMNE, is the favourite in the competition for new party leader. The party's national congress will take place at the weekend. (Dnevnik, Utrinski Vesnik - 20/05/03; MIA, A1 TV - 19/05/03)
